# Block secrets / personal overrides…
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
# …but keep the mode-scoped, non-secret defaults versioned. Vite loads
# `.env.development` automatically with `vite dev` and `.env.production`
# with `vite build`. The values are just public URLs (VITE_API_URL,
# VITE_API_TARGET) — they're not secrets and should travel with the repo.
!.env.example
!.env.development
!.env.production

